docs.name: [Chroma] Walk The Moon - Different Colors
docs.description:
Pretty happy with how this map turned out. This is by far my best lighting job, and I also like the other things I did with Chroma. Too lazy to do all the walls however, lmao

This map took just under 8 hours collectively to finish over the course of several days and am very happy with how it turned out. I put a lot of time into the mapping, lighting, and all of the Chroma effects that were included throughout the map.

BPM: 192
NJS: 20
JD: 18.5
Notes: 1146
Bombs: 32
Walls: 53
Lighting Events: 8335
NPS: 5.12
SPS: 4.20 (nice)

Don't know what else to say about this map, so hope you enjoy it :D

docs.name: Bad Habits - Ed Sheeran (Chroma+)
docs.description:
**Warning:** Chroma Note Coloring is very important for the "Bad Poodles and Bloqs". You can still use your own custom colors.

Poodle and 2 normal bloq diffs. The "Bad Poodles and Bloqs" diffs are special versions of the top diffs. Some have said its amazing, some think its a war crime, I say why not both.
Comes with a lightshow diff since Zen mode wont work (the moon is actually a bloq...bomb...both).

Again, huge thanks to @Phoenix for making environments like the one I used here. You can find and use them for free at the github https://github.com/Phoenix-BS/BSCEL

Thanks for the playtests MadChase, mochichi72, TheCzar1994, earblind69, VirtualStella,  vanitygirl_vr, suziescum, HyperSonicSharkz, CrazyOtterLady, ThatsJodie, Dietah, GeneralDum, TinkerVr85 and anyone I may have forgot.
